n_neighbors affects dimension r stress

Justin Lin

2023-09-06

get_var = function(name, num) {
  get(paste(name, num, sep=""))
}
Z = cbind(matrix(rnorm(100*6, sd = 5), nrow = 100), matrix(0, nrow = 100, ncol = 4)) + 
  matrix(rnorm(100*10, sd = 1), nrow = 100)
vars = diag(var(Z))

r = c(2,4,6,8,10)
k = 10

for (i in 1:length(r)) {
  assign(paste("pca", i, sep = ""), prcomp(Z, center = TRUE, rank = r[i]))
  assign(paste("Y", i, sep=""), get_var("pca", i)$x)
  assign(paste("Y_emb", i, sep=""),
         t(t(get_var("Y", i) %*% t(get_var("pca", i)$rotation)) + get_var("pca", i)$center))
}

n = dim(Z)[1]
p = dim(Z)[2]
q = 2

var_explained = pca1$sdev^2 / sum(pca1$sdev^2)
plot(var_explained)
lines(var_explained)

n_neighbors = c(18, 20, 22, 24, 26, 28, 30)

for (i in 1:length(n_neighbors)) {
  assign(paste("trans_umap", i, sep=""), umap(Z, method = 'umap-learn', n_neighbors = n_neighbors[i], n_components = q))
  assign(paste("X_umap", i, sep=""), eval(parse(text = paste("trans_umap", i, sep="")))$layout)
}
